{%- comment -%}
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PRODUCT BADGES COMPONENT
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This component is used in product listing and product page to render the badges of a given product

********************************************
Supported variables
********************************************

* product: the product to render the badges
* types: the types of badge to output. Can be "custom", "coming_soon", "sold_out" or "discount" (or a combination separated by comma). If nothing is set, all badges are outputted.
* form_id: an optional form ID to use to update the badges when a given variant changes
* block: an optional block to output theme editor attributes
* class: an extra class added on the container
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign badge_types = types | default: 'custom, coming_soon, new_release, sold_out, discount' | split: ',' -%}
{%- assign variant = product.selected_or_first_available_variant -%}

{%- comment -%}
Custom vcollect: an unreleased product has no stock yet, so Shopify reports it as unavailable and the theme would label
it "En rupture". That wrongly reads as "we sold out" on a product that was never on sale. The coming soon badge replaces
the sold out one rather than stacking with it.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- capture is_coming_soon -%}{%- render 'coming-soon-check', product: product -%}{%- endcapture -%}
{%- assign is_coming_soon = is_coming_soon | strip -%}

{%- comment -%}
Custom vcollect: an unreleased product that already has stock can be bought right away as a pre-order, so labelling it
"Bientôt disponible" would send the shopper away from a product that is on sale. The badge follows the same rule as the
buy buttons (see 'pre-order-check') so the two can never disagree.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- capture is_pre_order -%}{%- render 'pre-order-check', product: product -%}{%- endcapture -%}
{%- assign is_pre_order = is_pre_order | strip -%}

{%- comment -%}
Custom vcollect: same source of truth on the other side of the release date. A product stops being "Bientôt disponible"
and becomes "Nouveauté" on its release day, then stops being new once the window closes, all without an edit.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- capture is_new_release -%}{%- render 'new-release-check', product: product -%}{%- endcapture -%}
{%- assign is_new_release = is_new_release | strip -%}

{%- capture badges -%}
  {%- for badge_type in badge_types -%}
    {%- assign stripped_badge_type = badge_type | strip -%}

    {%- case stripped_badge_type -%}
      {%- when 'custom' -%}
        {%- assign custom_badges = product.metafields.custom.badges.value | sort -%}

        {%- for custom_badge in custom_badges -%}
          <span class="badge badge--primary">{{ custom_badge }}</span>
        {%- endfor -%}

      {%- when 'coming_soon' -%}
        {%- if is_pre_order == 'true' -%}
          <span class="badge badge--primary">{{ 'product.general.pre_order_badge' | t }}</span>
        {%- elsif is_coming_soon == 'true' -%}
          <span class="badge badge--primary">{{ 'product.general.coming_soon_badge' | t }}</span>
        {%- endif -%}

      {%- when 'new_release' -%}
        {%- if is_new_release == 'true' -%}
          <span class="badge badge--primary">{{ 'product.general.new_release_badge' | t }}</span>
        {%- endif -%}

      {%- when 'sold_out' -%}
        {%- if settings.show_sold_out_badge and is_coming_soon != 'true' -%}
          {%- if variant.available == false or form_id != blank -%}
            <sold-out-badge {% if variant.available %}hidden{% endif %} {% if form_id != blank %}form="{{ form_id }}"{% endif %} class="badge badge--sold-out">
              {{- 'product.general.sold_out_badge' | t -}}
            </sold-out-badge>
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endif -%}

      {%- when 'discount' -%}
        {%- if settings.show_discount -%}
          {%- assign is_variant_on_sale = false -%}

          {%- if variant.available and variant.compare_at_price > variant.price -%}
            {%- assign is_variant_on_sale = true -%}
          {%- endif -%}

          {%- if form_id != blank or is_variant_on_sale -%}
            {%- if settings.discount_mode == 'percentage' -%}
              {%- assign savings = variant.compare_at_price | minus: variant.price | times: 100.0 | divided_by: variant.compare_at_price | round | append: '%' -%}
            {%- else -%}
              {%- capture savings -%}{{ variant.compare_at_price | minus: variant.price | money }}{%- endcapture -%}
            {%- endif -%}

            {%- comment -%}
            When showing for product card (form_id == blank) and that the product price varies, we show a sale badge without explicit saving
            as it can cause confusion
            {%- endcomment -%}
            <on-sale-badge {% unless is_variant_on_sale %}hidden{% endunless %} {% if settings.show_discount %}discount-mode="{{ settings.discount_mode | escape }}"{% endif %} {% if form_id != blank %}form="{{ form_id }}"{% endif %} class="badge badge--on-sale">
              {%- if form_id == blank and product.price_varies -%}
                {{- 'product.general.on_sale_badge' | t -}}
              {%- else -%}
                {{- 'product.general.discount_badge_html' | t: savings: savings -}}
              {%- endif -%}
            </on-sale-badge>
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endif -%}
    {%- endcase -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endcapture -%}

{%- if badges != blank -%}
  <div class="{{ class }}" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
    {{- badges -}}
  </div>
{%- endif -%}